Storyline: After an unexpected family tragedy, three generations of the Deetz family return home to Winter River. Still haunted by Beetlejuice, Lydia's life is turned upside down when her rebellious teenage daughter, Astrid, discovers the mysterious model of the town in the attic and the portal to the Afterlife is accidentally opened. With trouble brewing in both realms, it's only a matter of time until someone says Beetlejuice's name three times and the mischievous demon returns to unleash his very own brand of mayhem.

After resigning and hiding in a remote estate with a new identity, Captain Sama Akl once again becomes entangled with the same gang, this time with Louay Al-Deeb, who seeks revenge for his father and cousin. This pushes her to do the impossible to confront Louay in order to protect herself and her daughter. Will she triumph over him, or will he triumph over her, or will something unexpected happen between them?.

Movie Name: The Black Tape Project - Texas Swim Week 2024

Storyline: Soun Tendou runs the Tendou Martial Arts School accompanied by his three daughters: Akane, Nabiki, and Kasumi. One day, the sisters' lives are turned upside down when their father announces that he has promised one of them to be married to a fellow martial artist's son in hopes of carrying on the family legacy. In addition to their mixed reactions, when the fiancé arrives, the last thing the Tendou family expects is Ranma Saotome and his father, Genma. Ranma has been training in China with his father until an unfortunate accident changed them both. Now, when water touches them, Ranma turns into a girl and Genma into a giant panda. Ranma ½ follows Ranma as he attempts to get along with his newly betrothed, the youngest of the Tendou sisters, Akane. As the two begin to attend the same school, they deal with fellow friends and rivals, all of whom have something to say about their engagement.

Movie Name: Emily Rinaudo's Black Tape Project Exclusive: Texas Swim Week 2024
